    <briefdescription>
<para>Utility class to perform XACC IR -&gt; CUDAQ Quake IR (MLIR-based) conversion. This is performed by implementing an <computeroutput>AllGateVisitor</computeroutput> and constructing the corresponding Quake IR node using CUDAQ&apos;s kernel_builder utility. This can also handle (classical) argument conversion (parameterized quantum circuit). Notes: (1) XACC IR (CompositeInstruction) only accepts a single kernel argument of type: double or std::vector&lt;double&gt;. Quake IR (MLIR) can accepts a much wider range of types and not limit the number of arguments. (2) The argument evaluation is XACC IR is very rudimentary. (based on the C++ Mathematical Expression Parsing And Evaluation Library, <ulink url="https://github.com/ArashPartow/exprtk">https://github.com/ArashPartow/exprtk</ulink>) Hence, we need to do a &apos;hacky&apos; conversion into QUAKE IR only supporting scaling (by multiplication) an argument in a rotation angle. e.g., Ry(0.1234*theta, q[0]), where theta is a parameterized angle bound to argument &apos;theta&apos;. </para>
    </briefdescription>
